     8→// ⟦axs_behavior⟧
     9→. *Connect Container to Enclave Network*:
    10→.. {rbbc_call}
    11→podman network connect to attach
    12→{at_sentry_container}
    13→to
    14→{at_enclave_network}
    15→.. {rbbc_require}
    16→successful network attachment
    17→.. {rbbc_require}
    18→interface naming sequence: eth0 is transit network, eth1 is enclave network
    19→
    20→. *Verify Network Interface Configuration*:
    21→.. {rbbc_call}
    22→{mkc_interface_check}
    23→with interface `eth1` and timeout_s `5` within sentry container context
    24→.. {rbbc_require}
    25→interface active before timeout
    26→.. {rbbc_fatal}
    27→if timeout reached: "Enclave network interface eth1 not active"
    28→
    29→. *Configure Sentry IP Address*:
    30→.. Remove auto-assigned IP address from eth1
    31→.. {rbbc_call}
    32→ip addr add to assign permanent
    33→{rbrn_enclave_sentry_ip}/{rbrn_enclave_netmask}
    34→to eth1
    35→.. {rbbc_store}
    36→`«SENTRY_IP»` as
    37→{rbrn_enclave_sentry_ip}
    38→.. NOTE: This address will serve as the gateway for the
    39→{at_bottle_container}
    40→after eBPF frame rewriting
    41→.. {rbbc_require}
    42→IP address configured successfully
    43→
    44→After this sequence completes, the
    45→{at_sentry_container}
    46→has connectivity on both networks with the correct IP configuration, ready to receive traffic from the
    47→{at_bottle_container}
    48→once the
    49→{at_ebpf_program}
    50→is attached.
